# Paths semgrep should not scan. (In a git repo semgrep already skips
# gitignored files, so these are belt-and-braces for local runs.)
node_modules/
dist/
dist-release/
out/
coverage/

# Two rules are excluded at the invocation site (--exclude-rule in the Security
# workflow and the `security` npm script) rather than here, because semgrepignore
# only filters paths, not rules:
#   - path-join-resolve-traversal — every hit joins a value already guarded by an
#     allowlist, safeId(), or a literal segment (src/main path stores + IPC).
#   - detect-non-literal-regexp — the only dynamic regexes are user-authored
#     workflow condition patterns, compiled inside try/catch (ReDoS-guarded).
# Both fire only false positives in this codebase. Drop the flag if that changes.
